article.story: STILLWATER, Okla. (AP) -- Daniel Bobik scored a game-high 23 points and three of his teammates scored in double digits to lead Oklahoma State to a 95-73 win over EA Sports in exhibition play Monday night. Tony Allen added 19 points for the Cowboys, who shot 50.7 percent from the field and 70 percent from the free-throw line. Joey Graham had 14 points and Ivan McFarlin added 10. The Cowboys, who led 44-39 at halftime, outrebounded EA Sports 55-38, with OSU's Jason Miller grabbing a game-high 10 rebounds, including nine defensive rebounds. John Lucas chipped in nine points for the Cowboys, Janover Weatherspoon had six, Stephen Graham had five and Miller had four points. Greg Minor led EA sports with 19 points. Brett McFall had 15, Koko Archibong had 13 and Nate Green added 12. McFall led all players with four assists.
